Organising the chaos of debate on Youtube.

The Youtube platform has, since its earliest inception, offered the opportunity for topics of interest to be ‘debated’.  Initially this was primarily through the use of the 'video response' function but since this was removed in 2014 debates have tended to take place more within Google Hangouts.

These are great, and having the whole debate in one place is definitely an advantage, but I think something has been lost in the mix; opportunities for reflection between responses, time to gather further research and get feedback, (Hangouts are also usually pretty long).

The idea here is that debates can take place in a way that takes the best of both previous systems.  After agreeing on a topic participants make videos of their Opening Statements which go live together on this channel.  They then have a period of time to consider what's been said and gather feedback then their Rebuttals are uploaded here, again going live at the same time.
